CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1967, pg. 13 reads: "AKA's All - In observance of Founders Day, members of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority gathered at Stouffer's Restaurant in Oakland for lunch and a special recognition service. Here some of them are pictured looking pretty for Courier photographer "Teenie" Harris.  They are AKA's all."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four women, including two holding plaque, seated on long dark sofa, with banner reading "Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Alpha Kappa Alpha Omega Chapter," in Stouffers Restaurant during Alpha Kappa Alpha Founders Day celebration
